a freight outlet.

03:20.408 --> 03:22.243
Jan, honey, come up here.
- All right, let's go.

03:22.285 --> 03:23.912
- Ready!

03:23.953 --> 03:27.749
- We're gonna show them how
nice Pocatello folk are, right?

03:27.791 --> 03:29.668
Grab your coat.

03:29.709 --> 03:31.044
Come here.

03:31.086 --> 03:35.882
<i>* *</i>

03:35.924 --> 03:37.217
We love you.

03:37.258 --> 03:39.052
- Okay, crew.

03:39.094 --> 03:44.182
Hup, two, three, four!
Hup, two, three, four!

03:44.224 --> 03:48.478
<i>* *</i>

03:48.520 --> 03:51.564
- Girls, it's only
two streets over. Let's walk.

03:51.606 --> 03:54.317
- Just down the street
that way.

03:54.359 --> 03:58.571
<i>* *</i>

03:58.613 --> 04:00.699
- So they have three boys,

04:00.740 --> 04:04.411
one Jan's age, one Karen's age,
and one Susan's age,

04:04.452 --> 04:06.413
and a little baby girl.
- Aww.

04:06.454 --> 04:09.332
Three boys and a baby girl.
- All right.

04:09.374 --> 04:12.085
<i>* *</i>

04:12.127 --> 04:15.213
- Hey, Jan.
- Hey, Brobergs.

04:15.255 --> 04:17.257
- Hey, Caroline.

04:17.298 --> 04:18.258
<i>* *</i>

04:18.299 --> 04:19.759
- Ah, dang.

04:19.801 --> 04:22.012
