07:38.458 --> 07:40.126
Okay.

07:43.338 --> 07:47.050
I was just a girl.

07:47.092 --> 07:48.760
My daddy was driving home
from the feed store

07:48.802 --> 07:51.221
in Brigham City one night.

07:51.262 --> 07:54.808
The moon went behind a cloud.

07:54.849 --> 07:59.104
And he sees these two lights
moving across the field.

07:59.145 --> 08:01.481
Not headlights.
They were going too fast.

08:01.523 --> 08:05.318
So he sped up.

08:05.360 --> 08:07.904
And then he says to himself,

08:07.946 --> 08:11.866
"Oh, my goodness.
They're chasing me."

08:13.243 --> 08:15.620
Then, his truck
starts to go cuckoo.

08:15.662 --> 08:17.414
The radio and the dials.

08:17.455 --> 08:20.875
And then it just conks out in
the middle of the road, dead.

08:20.917 --> 08:25.338
And those lights just set down
across the field,

08:25.380 --> 08:27.757
watching him.

08:28.675 --> 08:31.136
And then they take off.

08:31.177 --> 08:34.347
And they go up, up,
into the sky,

08:34.389 --> 08:36.474
until they're gone.

08:36.516 --> 08:37.684
The next morning,
my mother and I

08:37.726 --> 08:40.061
