what flowers

16:37.455 --> 16:40.041
to bring a ten-year-old girl
for her first choir solo.

16:40.083 --> 16:41.710
- Is Ruthie ten already?

16:41.751 --> 16:43.712
- I feel like I'll blink, and
she'll be grown and married.

16:43.753 --> 16:46.047
- Well, every day is a bonus.
I've always said.

16:46.089 --> 16:47.590
[phone rings]
Oh, pardon me one second.

16:47.632 --> 16:48.591
- Sure.

16:48.633 --> 16:51.678
<i>* *</i>

16:51.720 --> 16:53.430
[phone rings]

16:54.514 --> 16:56.224
- Atkins Florist.
What can I do for you?

16:56.266 --> 16:58.226
<i>- Good morning, Broberg.</i>
<i>How are you?</i>

16:58.268 --> 17:00.895
- Oh. Fine, B.

17:00.937 --> 17:03.189
And yourself?
<i>- Oh, I'm great.</i>

17:03.606 --> 17:05.525
I was just calling to make sure
it'd be all right with you

17:05.567 --> 17:10.113
if I took Jan horseback riding
after her piano lesson.

17:10.155 --> 17:11.322
- We already have plans.

17:11.364 --> 17:12.907
We're doing a puzzle
this evening.

17:12.949 --> 17:15.285
<i>- Aww, dang. That's--</i>

17:16.745 --> 17:18.371
You know, the thing is,
I promised her,

17:18.413 --> 17:20.165
and, oh,
I hate to disappoint her.

17:20.206 --> 17:21.541
<i>You know how Jan gets</i>

17:21.583 --> 17:23.501
<i>when she's got</i>
<i>her heart set on something.</i>

17:23.543 --> 17:25.962
- Well, sorry, B.
It'll have to be another time.

17:26.004 --> 17:28.089
Have a good day now. Bye, bye.
<i>- No, Bob--</i>

17:29.049 --> 17:33.428
- Now, you cannot go wrong
with some long-stem roses.

17:38.099 --> 17:40.685
[phone rings]

17:40.727 --> 17:42.062
- Hello, Brobergs.

17:42.103 --> 17:44.856
- Gosh, Mary Ann,
you sound so blue.

17:44.898 --> 17:46.399
- Hi, B.

17:46.441 --> 17:49.194
I'm not blue at all.
How are you?

17:49.235 --> 17:51.905
- Oh, well,
now that you mention it,

17:51.946 --> 17:54.324
I skipped breakfast,

17:54.366 --> 17:57.494
and I am a bit peckish.

17:59.454 --> 18:02.582
- Well, you just
hold your horses.

18:06.544 --> 18:09.297
- Bob's always bragging
about his sandwiches.

18:09.339 --> 18:10.882
I think you're the real artist
in the house.

18:10.924 --> 18:13.259
- [chuckles] It's just
what's in the fridge.

18:13.301 --> 18:15.512
- It's how you put it together.

18:15.553 --> 18:18.348
I don't know how you do it.

18:18.390 --> 18:23.937
You sure are special, Mary Ann.
You know that?

18:23.978 --> 18:25.230
Hey.

18:25.271 --> 18:28.191
<i>[country music on stereo]</i>

18:28.233 --> 18:30.193
<i>* *</i>

18:30.235 --> 18:32.070
Are you sure you're not blue?

18:32.112 --> 18:36.324
<i>* *</i>

18:36.366 --> 18:38.118
Why don't I take you
for birthday milkshakes

18:38.159 --> 18:41.246
with the girls this weekend?

18:41.287 --> 18:43.456
That might cheer you up.

18:43.498 --> 18:47.460
- It sure would.
[chuckles]

18:47.502 --> 18:49.129
Maybe afterwards, we could--
- Before I forget.

18:49.170 --> 18:51.506
Before I forget.

18:51.548 --> 18:53.883
I promised Jan that
I'd take her horseback riding

18:53.925 --> 18:56.136
in American Falls
after her piano lesson.

18:56.177 --> 18:57.554
She's getting pretty good.

18:57.595 --> 18:59.389
- Tonight?
- Yeah.

18:59.431 --> 19:03.518
Yeah, I'd have her back
by 6:30, 7:00 at the latest.

19:03.560 --> 19:05.979
- That should be all right.
I better ask Bob.

19:06.021 --> 19:07.647
- Sure. Sure.

19:07.689 --> 19:09.024
<i>- * You leave me</i>
<i>nothing else to do *</i>

19:09.065 --> 19:12.986
<i>* But tell you to go on</i>
<i>but I still love you *</i>

19:13.028 --> 19:17.282
<i>* Restless woman *</i>

19:17.323 --> 19:21.536
<i>* Oh, woman *</i>

19:21.578 --> 19:25.290
<i>* Restless woman *</i>

19:25.331 --> 19:27.625
[phone ringing]

19:27.667 --> 19:29.669
- Atkins Florist,
what can I do for you?

19:29.711 --> 19:31.713
<i>- Hi, hon.</i>
<i>How are things at the shop?</i>

19:31.755 --> 19:34.632
- Oh, pretty good.
Got some nice carnations in.

19:34.674 --> 19:37.510
- B wants to take Jan horseback
riding in American Falls

19:37.552 --> 19:39.387
tonight after piano.

19:39.429 --> 19:41.139
<i>She might be a little late</i>
<i>for dinner,</i>

19:41.181 --> 19:43.475
<i>but that's no problem, right?</i>

19:43.516 --> 19:46.770
- Actually, it is a problem.
I already told him no.

19:46.811 --> 19:49.522
- I didn't realize that.

19:49.564 --> 19:51.066
Do you think maybe
you ought to reconsider?

19:51.107 --> 19:52.275
You know how upset she'll be.

19:52.317 --> 19:54.319
<i>And she's getting really good.</i>

19:54.361 --> 19:57.530
- I said no,
and the answer is still no.

19:57.572 --> 19:59.115
<i>- You don't have to get testy.</i>

19:59.157 --> 20:03.620
I just think you might be being
a little bit unreasonable.

20:03.661 --> 20:05.997
<i>If you could ride horses,</i>
<i>you could take Jan yourself.</i>

20:06.039 --> 20:07.290
- I'm allergic to horses!

20:07.332 --> 20:08.583
- Well, B isn't.

20:09.751 --> 20:12.879
- [sighs]
Mary Ann, who is her father?

20:12.921 --> 20:14.297
Him or me?

20:16.132 --> 20:19.135
- You are, Bob.

20:19.177 --> 20:20.720
<i>[soft pleasant music]</i>

20:20.762 --> 20:22.180
- One Mississippi,
two Mississippi,

20:22.222 --> 20:23.264
three Mississippi,

20:23.306 --> 20:25.058
four Mississippi,
five Mississippi.

20:25.100 --> 20:28.269
[children chanting, clapping]
Concentration...64.

20:28.311 --> 20:30.063
- Lion.

20:30.105 --> 20:31.314
- Cat.

20:31.356 --> 20:38.446
<i>* *</i>

20:44.035 --> 20:46.913
[both chuckle]

20:50.542 --> 20:53.461
<i>[ominous music]</i>

20:53.503 --> 21:00.635
<i>* *</i>

21:09.978 --> 21:12.939
<i>- Ed Stephens.</i>
<i>Just the man I need to see.</i>

21:12.981 --> 21:15.900
<i>- Howdy, Bob.</i>
<i>What can I help you with?</i>

21:16.985 --> 21:21.072
- Oh, just need
to deposit a check.

21:21.114 --> 21:24.367
$27,208.43.

21:24.409 --> 21:26.453
- Good grief, Bob.

21:26.494 --> 21:28.455
Where'd you get a chunk
of change like this?

21:28.496 --> 21:31.541
- Well, I sold the store.

21:34.210 --> 21:36.004
Need to make a withdrawal, too.

21:36.046 --> 21:43.053
<i>* *</i>

21:43.511 --> 21:46.473
[machine whirring]

21:46.514 --> 21:50.810
<i>* *</i>

21:50.852 --> 21:53.605
- All right, here we go.
- [fusses]

21:55.231 --> 21:56.441
Good girl, Jenny.

21:57.859 --> 21:59.986
So good.

22:00.028 --> 22:03.239
- [fussing]

22:03.281 --> 22:05.742
- Bob.

22:05.784 --> 22:08.203
What are you doing home
in the middle of the day?

22:08.244 --> 22:10.955
- Oh, I'm just starved.

22:10.997 --> 22:14.292
Wanted to grab a bite

22:14.334 --> 22:16.169
while on my way back.

22:16.211 --> 22:22.342
<i>* *</i>

22:22.384 --> 22:26.054
- Back from where?

22:26.096 --> 22:33.061
<i>* *</i>

22:50.328 --> 22:53.123
- Gonna head back to the store
for the afternoon.

22:53.164 --> 22:56.126
I'll see you tonight.

22:56.167 --> 22:59.629
<i>* *</i>

22:59.671 --> 23:01.589
[engine turns over]

23:01.631 --> 23:08.763
<i>* *</i>

23:15.687 --> 23:18.732
- Pick out a good horse for me.
- I will.

23:23.153 --> 23:24.571
- Come on.

23:25.822 --> 23:26.990
- Will you keep my dinner
in the oven

23:27.032 --> 23:28.533
in case I get home
a little late

23:28.575 --> 23:30.410
from horseback riding
with Brother B?

23:30.452 --> 23:32.579
After piano?

23:32.620 --> 23:34.497
- It's gonna have to be
another day for that.

23:34.539 --> 23:36.833
- Another day?

23:36.875 --> 23:38.418
How come?

23:38.460 --> 23:42.714
- Jan, we're having dinner
tonight and doing a puzzle.

23:42.756 --> 23:45.008
Plus, I guess we have been

23:45.050 --> 23:47.635
spending a bit too much
with Brother B and his family.

23:48.094 --> 23:49.220
both: No, we haven't!

23:49.262 --> 23:51.598
- You spend all your time
with Sister Gail.

23:51.639 --> 23:53.224
And a lot with Brother B.

23:56.311 --> 23:58.480
- That is true.

23:58.521 --> 24:01.316
But still, your father thinks
it's time for a little break.

24:01.358 --> 24:03.902
- He's just mad he can't do
the things we can do.

24:05.070 --> 24:06.029
It's not fair.

24:09.532 --> 24:11.451
- [sighs]

24:11.493 --> 24:14.204
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

24:14.245 --> 24:21.169
<i>* *</i>

24:39.771 --> 24:41.648
- Hi there, ma'am.

24:41.690 --> 24:44.067
I am here
to escort a young lady

24:44.109 --> 24:46.778
to a piano lesson
and then to ride a horse.

24:46.820 --> 24:49.864
- I wasn't expecting you, B.

24:49.906 --> 24:53.034
I think there's been
a misunderstanding.

24:53.076 --> 24:55.662
- Thought I heard your voice.
- Yeah, you thought right.

24:55.704 --> 24:57.664
How was school?
- Pretty good.

24:57.706 --> 24:59.958
Now horseback riding?

25:01.918 --> 25:05.338
- B, didn't Bob tell you that
tonight wasn't gonna work?

25:05.380 --> 25:06.756
- Oh, you know Bob.

25:06.798 --> 25:09.676
Back and forth
till your head spins.

25:09.718 --> 25:11.553
- I'm afraid he still says no.

25:18.351 --> 25:21.062
- Sure wish Bob wouldn't be
so strict with her.

25:21.104 --> 25:22.731
- Why don't we all just
do something together

25:22.772 --> 25:25.108
this weekend?

25:25.150 --> 25:27.861
Or how about I bring you
another sandwich

25:27.902 --> 25:30.363
tomorrow at the store?

25:30.405 --> 25:33.366
I like our talks.
- Yeah.

25:33.408 --> 25:35.744
Well, that sounds great.

25:35.785 --> 25:40.707
Meantime, what are we gonna
tell that little girl?

25:40.749 --> 25:41.958
- It doesn't even make sense

25:42.000 --> 25:44.044
for you to take her
to piano now.

25:44.085 --> 25:47.047
I have to take Karen and Susan
to choir practice anyway.

25:47.088 --> 25:48.840
- [chuckles]

25:48.882 --> 25:51.134
I don't even want to go
horseback riding for myself.

25:51.176 --> 25:53.470
Jasper asked me to build
a bookcase for his room.

25:53.511 --> 25:57.640
I'm neglecting my own boy just
so I can keep my word to Jan.

25:57.682 --> 25:59.976
- B.

26:00.018 --> 26:01.644
- [groans]
For Pete's sake.

26:01.686 --> 26:04.814
I don't care who takes her.
You take her to the lesson.

26:04.856 --> 26:05.940
I'll go home
and play with the boys.

26:05.982 --> 26:08.026
I'll pick her up after.

26:08.068 --> 26:10.904
The only thing I care about

26:10.945 --> 26:14.866
is not disappointing
a little girl.

26:14.908 --> 26:17.619
You know what that's like.

26:17.660 --> 26:20.497
Just wanting something so bad.

26:20.538 --> 26:21.956
Don't you, Mary Ann?

26:23.083 --> 26:26.211
<i>[sparse ominous music]</i>

26:26.252 --> 26:30.215
<i>* *</i>

26:30.256 --> 26:34.761
[softly] Hey.

26:34.803 --> 26:37.722
Do you remember
what I told you?

26:37.764 --> 26:40.684
[indistinct whispering]

26:40.725 --> 26:47.816
<i>* *</i>

26:53.822 --> 26:57.325
[footsteps thudding]

26:59.244 --> 27:02.789
Jan, I'll see you after
your piano lesson.

27:02.831 --> 27:06.084
But we need to be home
by 6:30 sharp.

27:06.126 --> 27:09.004
- Yes!

27:17.679 --> 27:19.681
[door opens]

27:36.823 --> 27:38.533
- Bob Berchtold's gonna
pick her up

27:38.575 --> 27:40.827
to go horseback riding
when she's finished today.

27:40.869 --> 27:43.329
- That sounds fun.

27:43.371 --> 27:47.042
<i>* *</i>

27:47.083 --> 27:49.336
Did you practice this week?

27:49.377 --> 27:50.879
- Yes, ma'am.

27:50.920 --> 27:58.053
<i>* *</i>

28:15.737 --> 28:18.656
[Bach's "Minuet in G Minor"]

28:18.698 --> 28:20.950
* *

28:20.992 --> 28:22.285
- Don't look at your hands.

28:22.327 --> 28:25.246
Read your music,
and put your hands like--

28:25.288 --> 28:27.624
yes, perfect.

28:27.665 --> 28:29.709
Okay.

28:29.751 --> 28:31.294
Those horses
aren't going anywhere,

28:31.336 --> 28:32.712
and the more you look
at that clock,

28:32.754 --> 28:34.381
the slower times goes.

28:34.422 --> 28:35.799
Again.

28:37.258 --> 28:41.930
* *

28:41.971 --> 28:44.432
- He's here!
- What? Uh--

28:44.474 --> 28:47.394
<i>[soft pleasant music]</i>

28:47.435 --> 28:49.771
<i>* *</i>

28:49.813 --> 28:51.439
- What took you so long?

28:51.481 --> 28:53.817
These horses aren't
gonna wait forever.

28:53.858 --> 28:56.403
- I'm not late.
- [chuckling] Oh.

28:56.444 --> 29:03.368
<i>* *</i>

29:04.202 --> 29:06.788
[sighs]

29:08.415 --> 29:11.918
Oh. Almost forgot.

29:11.960 --> 29:15.422
Your allergy pill.

29:15.463 --> 29:18.466
- Look. I can take it
without water.

29:23.972 --> 29:28.727
- You are something else.
You know that?

29:28.768 --> 29:30.770
All right. Giddy up.

29:30.812 --> 29:37.944
<i>* *</i>

29:44.451 --> 29:48.121
<i>- * I've always got</i>
<i>a smilin' face *</i>

29:48.163 --> 29:51.541
<i>* Any time and any place *</i>

29:51.583 --> 29:53.877
<i>* And every time</i>
<i>they ask me why *</i>

29:53.918 --> 29:57.756
<i>* I just smile and say *</i>

29:57.797 --> 29:59.382
<i>* You've got to... *</i>

29:59.424 --> 30:02.635
- * Kiss an angel
good morning *

30:02.677 --> 30:07.390
* And let her know you think
about her when you're gone *

30:07.432 --> 30:10.602
* You kiss an angel
good morning *

30:10.643 --> 30:14.731
* And love her like the devil
when you get back home *

30:14.773 --> 30:17.317
- [laughing]
Oh, my gosh.

30:17.359 --> 30:19.652
If you were in a choir,
they'd kick you out.

30:19.694 --> 30:21.071
[giggles]

30:21.112 --> 30:22.697
<i>- * The secret</i>
<i>of a happiness *</i>

30:22.739 --> 30:25.158
- Well, the way
I see it, dolly,

30:25.200 --> 30:26.826
whatever voice
you're blessed with,

30:26.868 --> 30:30.622
you gotta sing with that voice.

30:30.663 --> 30:32.499
- Yeah.

30:32.540 --> 30:33.625
I guess you're right.

30:33.667 --> 30:35.168
<i>- * The secret</i>
<i>I'm speakin' of *</i>

30:35.210 --> 30:38.672
<i>* Is a woman and a man</i>
<i>in love *</i>

30:38.713 --> 30:39.839
<i>* And the answer is... *</i>

30:39.881 --> 30:43.593
- B?
- Yes, dolly.

30:43.635 --> 30:45.011
- I'm glad we're friends.

30:45.053 --> 30:51.017
<i>- * You've got to</i>
<i>kiss an angel good mornin' *</i>

30:51.059 --> 30:54.396
- Me too, honey.

30:54.437 --> 30:55.605
Me too.

30:55.647 --> 30:58.066
<i>- * Kiss an angel</i>
<i>good mornin' *</i>

30:58.108 --> 31:01.403
<i>* And lover her like the devil</i>
<i>when you get back home *</i>

31:01.444 --> 31:03.363
- World sure would be
a nice place to live

31:03.405 --> 31:07.826
if everybody could just have
a friendship like we do.

31:07.867 --> 31:10.870
To be who you are,

31:10.912 --> 31:13.331
and do what makes you happy.

31:13.373 --> 31:17.002
- [yawns]

31:17.043 --> 31:19.713
Yeah.

31:19.754 --> 31:22.257
That sounds nice.

31:22.298 --> 31:25.427
<i>[soft pleasant music]</i>

31:25.468 --> 31:32.392
<i>* *</i>

32:31.409 --> 32:33.536
- Is chicken almost ready?

32:33.578 --> 32:36.956
- Five minutes.
Go wash your hands.

32:36.998 --> 32:39.000
You too, Susie Q.

32:46.007 --> 32:47.092
- Where's Jani?

32:47.133 --> 32:49.010
- Oh, she should be home
any minute.

32:49.052 --> 32:50.762
You know, she just had
her heart set on

32:50.804 --> 32:52.222
horseback riding tonight.

32:55.016 --> 32:57.894
- Well, dang it, Mary Ann.

32:57.936 --> 33:00.897
We discussed this, didn't we?

33:00.939 --> 33:05.318
- Yes, but then B came by
the house after school,

33:05.360 --> 33:09.572
and Jan just got so excited.

33:09.614 --> 33:12.117
- How am I supposed to lead
this family

33:12.158 --> 33:14.577
if every time
I put my foot down,

33:14.619 --> 33:16.705
you go and just--

33:16.746 --> 33:19.165
- I'm sorry.

33:19.207 --> 33:22.836
I made him promise
they'd be home by 6:30.

33:22.877 --> 33:25.714
- Where are they?

33:25.755 --> 33:28.758
<i>[ominous music]</i>

33:28.800 --> 33:31.845
[crickets chirping]

33:31.886 --> 33:38.810
<i>* *</i>

33:55.452 --> 33:57.704
- If we're not gonna
do the puzzle,

33:57.746 --> 34:00.248
can we watch
"The Waltons" at 8:00?

34:00.290 --> 34:02.417
- Yes.
But finish your homework first.

34:11.092 --> 34:12.052
- What was the name
of the ranch

34:12.093 --> 34:13.386
where they went riding?

34:13.428 --> 34:15.847
Gail would know, wouldn't she?

34:17.182 --> 34:24.022
<i>* *</i>

34:24.064 --> 34:26.358
[phone ringing]

34:26.399 --> 34:28.902
[indistinct chatter]
- Boys, hush.

34:28.943 --> 34:31.571
[phone ringing]

34:31.613 --> 34:32.739
Yes?

34:32.781 --> 34:36.368
<i>- Hi, Gail.</i>
<i>It's Mary Ann and Bob.</i>

34:36.409 --> 34:40.246
- Oh, hi, Mary Ann.
What's going on?

34:40.288 --> 34:43.333
<i>- We're a bit worried,</i>
<i>to be honest.</i>

34:43.375 --> 34:46.836
<i>B was supposed to bring</i>
<i>Jan back an hour ago.</i>

34:46.878 --> 34:50.882
- I hope they haven't had
a flat or anything like that.

34:50.924 --> 34:54.427
- Oh, I--I hope not.

34:54.469 --> 34:56.721
- I bet they lost track
of time is all.

34:56.763 --> 35:00.183
You know how Jan loves
that old paint horse.

35:00.225 --> 35:02.894
<i>- The one at my brother</i>
<i>Keith's ranch?</i>

35:04.062 --> 35:06.231
But I'm sure he said

35:06.272 --> 35:09.192
they were going
to American Falls.

35:09.234 --> 35:12.821
<i>He told me about a customer</i>
<i>who has a ranch out that way?</i>

35:12.862 --> 35:14.531
- Oh, I see.

35:15.990 --> 35:19.160
- Gail, this is Bob.
I don't like this one bit.

35:21.830 --> 35:23.748
- I think it would be better
if I just come over there

35:23.790 --> 35:26.126
and we can talk
about this in person.

35:26.167 --> 35:28.962
Would that be all right?

35:29.004 --> 35:30.839
- Yeah, okay.

35:30.880 --> 35:32.382
<i>[ominous music]</i>

35:32.424 --> 35:35.468
- Boys.
Boys, look at me.

35:35.510 --> 35:38.096
I have to go to the Brobergs.
Watch your sister for me.

35:38.138 --> 35:41.016
- [grunting]
- Get off me!

35:41.057 --> 35:43.018
<i>* *</i>

35:43.059 --> 35:46.021
[dog barking]

35:46.062 --> 35:53.194
<i>* *</i>

36:04.706 --> 36:05.832
- Gail, hi.

36:05.874 --> 36:06.916
- Hello.

36:06.958 --> 36:08.835
<i>[indistinct chatter on TV]</i>

36:08.877 --> 36:11.004
- Come on in.
Can I get you something?

36:11.046 --> 36:13.548
- Oh, no. I'm okay.

36:13.590 --> 36:18.136
So I just remembered
walking over.

36:18.178 --> 36:22.265
Do you remember when he drove
the kids to Salt Lake City?

36:22.307 --> 36:24.184
But they wanted to go
to the circus,

36:24.225 --> 36:29.731
so they stayed overnight,
and he came back the next day.

36:29.773 --> 36:31.358
- Have a seat.

36:31.399 --> 36:34.402
- Yeah, but he called
to tell us.

36:34.444 --> 36:36.696
And it wasn't a school night.

36:36.738 --> 36:40.367
- Well, he may still call.
It's only 8:00.

36:40.408 --> 36:43.078
- It's not like B.

36:43.119 --> 36:45.538
- Well, you know he gets.

36:45.580 --> 36:47.624
- You mean his depression?

36:47.665 --> 36:50.919
- Manic depression is what
the doctors call it.

36:50.960 --> 36:53.046
One minute,
he can be down in the dumps.

36:53.088 --> 36:58.510
And the next thing you know,
it's, whew, up like a rocket.

36:58.551 --> 37:02.263
He just, he gets so excited.

37:02.305 --> 37:03.848
- Are you saying that
he got excited

37:03.890 --> 37:07.310
and that they went
to the circus again?

37:08.436 --> 37:10.355
- Or it could be a flat.

37:10.397 --> 37:13.316
<i>[soft ominous music]</i>

37:13.358 --> 37:15.860
<i>* *</i>

37:15.902 --> 37:19.447
The only thing is--

37:19.489 --> 37:21.783
- What is it?

37:21.825 --> 37:24.577
<i>* *</i>

37:24.619 --> 37:26.371
- Gail, if you have
something to say,

37:26.413 --> 37:28.998
I think you better say it.

37:29.040 --> 37:33.086
- I'm sure it's nothing.

37:33.128 --> 37:36.589
For the past two weeks,

37:36.631 --> 37:39.134
he's been coming home
quite late,

37:39.175 --> 37:40.927
and I've been worried about
his well-being,

37:40.969 --> 37:45.306
so I followed him
out to our storage unit,

37:45.348 --> 37:48.601
where we keep our boat,

37:48.643 --> 37:53.273
and I could see him inside,
working on a motorhome.

37:53.314 --> 37:56.067
- I didn't know
you had a motorhome.

37:56.109 --> 37:58.278
- And neither did I.

37:58.319 --> 37:59.821
- Oh.

37:59.863 --> 38:05.326
- He gets...
these impulsive moods.

38:05.368 --> 38:08.329
- But he has Jan with him,
though,

38:08.371 --> 38:11.124
so he has to think
about her too.

38:11.166 --> 38:13.626
That's the main thing.

38:13.668 --> 38:16.171
I know that he would
never intentionally

38:16.212 --> 38:19.841
do anything to upset us, but...

38:19.883 --> 38:22.302
- [sighs]

38:22.344 --> 38:24.262
I think we gotta
call the police,

38:24.304 --> 38:27.974
just to let them know that
Jan hasn't come home yet.

38:28.016 --> 38:29.142
<i>* *</i>

38:29.184 --> 38:30.894
- What?

38:30.935 --> 38:34.814
I mean, I'd hate to
cause all that trouble,

38:34.856 --> 38:38.318
when it's only been
just 90 minutes.

38:38.360 --> 38:39.986
<i>* *</i>

38:40.028 --> 38:42.572
And think how scared
Jan would be

38:42.614 --> 38:45.867
if the police come
and cause a fuss.

38:45.909 --> 38:47.702
<i>* *</i>

38:47.744 --> 38:50.830
Let's just give them
a little longer, all right?

38:50.872 --> 38:54.376
<i>* *</i>

38:54.417 --> 38:56.169
- I guess there isn't much
they can do

38:56.211 --> 38:57.879
after 90 minutes, is there?

38:57.921 --> 39:00.173
- [clears throat]

39:00.215 --> 39:03.176
Well...

39:03.218 --> 39:05.595
if he's been going out to the
storage unit every night

39:05.637 --> 39:07.055
to work on this motorhome,

39:07.097 --> 39:09.057
then maybe you ought
to take us there.

39:09.099 --> 39:13.228
Maybe he took Jani there
to, you know, show her.

39:13.269 --> 39:15.689
- Sure. I can do that.

39:15.730 --> 39:17.232
- How about Gail and I go,

39:17.273 --> 39:19.234
and you stay here
with the girls?

39:19.275 --> 39:20.652
Maybe he'll call.

39:20.694 --> 39:22.570
- Yeah. All right.

39:25.240 --> 39:28.785
Hey, Gail, could you give me
the number for the fella

39:28.827 --> 39:32.122
he's got working down
at the store, Bob Eldridge?

39:32.163 --> 39:35.458
If they did go riding
at some customer's ranch,

39:35.500 --> 39:39.087
I mean, he would know
who it was, wouldn't he?

39:39.129 --> 39:41.589
- Sure. Of course.
I can write it down.

39:43.466 --> 39:44.884
- Great.

39:44.926 --> 39:51.850
<i>* *</i>

39:53.727 --> 39:56.396
Good evening, Bob.
It's Bob Broberg.

39:56.438 --> 39:59.733
<i>- Oh, hi, Bob!</i>
<i>What's going on?</i>

39:59.774 --> 40:04.821
- Well, Berchtold--[sighs]

40:04.863 --> 40:07.991
Well, Berchtold went
and took Jan horseback riding,

40:08.033 --> 40:11.494
and they were supposed
to be back some time ago.

40:11.536 --> 40:13.913
It seems they went to a ranch

40:13.955 --> 40:16.207
that belongs
to a customer of yours?

40:16.249 --> 40:19.252
Does that ring a bell?
Do you know who that is?

40:19.294 --> 40:21.546
<i>- I can't say I know</i>
<i>a customer with a horse ranch.</i>

40:21.588 --> 40:23.173
<i>Not off hand.</i>

40:25.550 --> 40:27.594
- [sighs]

40:27.635 --> 40:31.598
Okay. All right.
Well, thank you for your help.

40:31.639 --> 40:34.476
<i>- Oh, don't worry, though.</i>
<i>You know how reliable he is.</i>

40:34.517 --> 40:37.771
<i>He's always saying how much</i>
<i>he thinks of you, Bob.</i>

40:37.812 --> 40:40.148
<i>He says, "Good old Broberg's</i>
<i>always there</i>

40:40.190 --> 40:41.566
<i>to give me a hand."</i>

40:46.154 --> 40:48.031
- You...

40:50.325 --> 40:51.659
Have a good night.

40:51.701 --> 40:58.833
<i>* *</i>

41:15.642 --> 41:17.644
- This one?

41:17.686 --> 41:19.896
- Yes. This is it right here.

41:39.541 --> 41:43.294
I guess I don't have the key.

42:00.645 --> 42:03.273
- What is it?

42:03.314 --> 42:05.233
Do you see it in there?

42:07.444 --> 42:09.195
- I can't see anything.

42:11.281 --> 42:12.574
We better get back home.

42:14.993 --> 42:17.328
- Just can't figure out why
he's got a motorhome in there

42:17.370 --> 42:18.663
without telling you.

42:53.448 --> 42:55.367
They didn't call?

42:57.077 --> 42:59.913
- Well, it must be car trouble.

42:59.954 --> 43:03.083
That's the only explanation.

43:03.124 --> 43:07.087
- I think we need to call
the police and let them know.

43:10.715 --> 43:12.133
- What'll you say?

43:12.175 --> 43:14.094
- Just that they were supposed
to be home by 6:30,

43:14.135 --> 43:16.304
and that we're getting a bit--
- Dad?

43:19.683 --> 43:20.975
- Yeah, Bright Eyes?

43:21.017 --> 43:24.479
- Did Jan and B come back yet?

43:24.521 --> 43:27.440
- Uh, no. No.

43:27.482 --> 43:28.817
Go on to bed now.

43:34.322 --> 43:39.160
- [sobbing]

43:41.246 --> 43:42.997
- What's wrong?

43:43.039 --> 43:45.000
- What's gotten into you, Gail?

43:49.879 --> 43:52.007
- I felt so bad.

43:53.383 --> 43:57.595
And we didn't
want to tell anyone.

43:57.637 --> 43:59.806
- Tell anyone what?

43:59.848 --> 44:02.183
- He's been struggling.

44:06.312 --> 44:09.482
There was this...

44:09.524 --> 44:13.862
little Mexican girl.

44:13.903 --> 44:17.532
You know how much
he loves children.

44:17.574 --> 44:21.202
And we've--we want another.

44:23.997 --> 44:27.334
Then, we heard about
this little girl down there.

44:27.375 --> 44:32.881
This Maria.

44:32.922 --> 44:34.841
Who needed a better life.

44:38.845 --> 44:42.849
So I flew down

44:42.891 --> 44:46.519
and met him with
all the adoption papers.

44:46.561 --> 44:48.605
[sighs]

44:48.646 --> 44:53.109
And she was cute as a button.

44:55.528 --> 44:59.074
But at the last minute...

44:59.115 --> 45:05.330
her mother just cried and cried

45:05.372 --> 45:06.956
and wouldn't let her go.

45:10.835 --> 45:13.046
[sighs]

45:14.255 --> 45:16.049
You should have seen
how disappointed he was

45:16.091 --> 45:18.760
that he had to
leave her in Mexico.

45:22.389 --> 45:25.642
- I had no idea.

45:25.684 --> 45:31.022
I guess that helps explain
his depression and so on.

45:38.279 --> 45:40.782
We still have
to call the police.

45:40.824 --> 45:43.785
- Oh, wait. Mary Ann.

45:43.827 --> 45:48.581
Wait until tomorrow.

45:48.623 --> 45:50.917
Whatever's got them delayed,

45:50.959 --> 45:53.545
he would never let anything
happen to her.

45:59.009 --> 46:02.220
And you know...

46:02.262 --> 46:04.806
he would never forgive you.

46:06.433 --> 46:13.356
<i>* *</i>

46:34.044 --> 46:37.172
[dial whirring]

46:45.347 --> 46:48.224
- [exhales shakily]
<i>[line ringing]</i>

46:48.266 --> 46:49.976
<i>- District 5,</i>
<i>Idaho State Police.</i>

46:50.018 --> 46:52.145
<i>What can I do for you?</i>

46:52.187 --> 46:57.275
- Well, I suppose I have
an inquiry for somebody there.

46:57.317 --> 46:58.902
<i>- Yes, ma'am.</i>
<i>What's your question?</i>

46:58.943 --> 47:02.155
- I was wondering
if anyone reported

47:02.197 --> 47:06.451
a car broken down
or an accident of some kind

47:06.493 --> 47:11.664
involving a green
1974 Ford Maverick.

47:11.706 --> 47:16.169
Anyone injured or...

47:16.211 --> 47:18.213
anything like that.

47:18.254 --> 47:19.964
<i>- I'll ask.</i>
<i>Hold on just a sec.</i>

47:20.006 --> 47:22.008
- Thank you.

47:22.050 --> 47:25.053
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

47:25.095 --> 47:32.185
<i>* *</i>

47:32.227 --> 47:34.562
<i>- Ma'am, I've got nothing</i>
<i>like that tonight.</i>

47:34.604 --> 47:36.564
- Oh, that's a relief.

47:43.029 --> 47:46.825
<i>- Is that all?</i>

47:46.866 --> 47:49.536
- Yes.

47:49.577 --> 47:50.787
Thank you.

47:50.829 --> 47:52.831
<i>- All right, then.</i>
<i>You have a good night.</i>

47:52.872 --> 47:54.457
- You have a good night, too.

47:58.128 --> 48:00.964
I'm sure they'll be back soon.

48:03.299 --> 48:05.093
He'll take good care of her.

48:05.135 --> 48:08.013
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

48:08.054 --> 48:15.186
<i>* *</i>

49:03.109 --> 49:06.112
- Good night, Mary Ann.

49:11.076 --> 49:13.495
- When they get back,

49:13.536 --> 49:16.081
you'll give him a piece
of your mind, won't you?

49:19.876 --> 49:21.503
- You're damn right, I will.

49:38.103 --> 49:41.731
<i>- Do you remember</i>
<i>what I told you?</i>

49:42.524 --> 49:45.485
Do you remember what I told you
at the Gold and Green Ball?

49:47.862 --> 49:50.198
I wish I had met you earlier.

49:51.950 --> 49:54.077
<i>You just hold your horses.</i>

49:55.870 --> 50:02.794
